textBeforeTable: Broadcast hosts will introduce listeners to the following Cure Kids Cancer Heroes and their courageous families. Tune in to listen March 23 – 25 from 6 a.m. to 6 p.m. as families call in or stop by to share personal and heartfelt stories about how their lives were changed by Sanford Children’s Hospital. Station hosts will also talk with doctors and staff. The radiothon is also available online on MIX 97.3, KIKN Country 100.5, B102.7 and HOT 104.7. The event which aims at helping kids fight cancer is being held March 23 – 25. During the 36 hour event, hosts from MIX 97.3, KIKN Country 100.5, B102.7, Hot 104.7 as well as KSOO 1130 and KDEZ 100.1, will broadcast live from the Carlson Great Hall at Sanford Children’s Hospital. (Sioux Falls, SD) – Cancer is a devastating disease, especially in children. It dramatically changes the lives of entire families and alters their childhood experiences. That’s why Sanford Children’s Hospital and Results Radio are teaming up once again for the 4th Annual Results Radio Cure Kids Cancer Radiothon. Last year’s event raised more than $161,000 and this year hopes are even higher. textAfterTable: Sanford Children’s Hospital in Sioux Falls, SD joined the Children’s Miracle Network team in 1986. As a Children’s Miracle Network hospital, Sanford Children’s Hospital in Sioux Falls stands dedicated to the ideal that every child is unique, every diagnosis is different and every situation is special. One hundred percent of funds raised stay local to help local children. As the areas only Cure Kids Cancer hospital, Sanford Children’s Hospital offers the region’s most comprehensive health care services for children. Leading edge technology, specially trained medical professionals and a vast array of services help meet the multiple medical needs of our patients and their families. Cure Kids Cancer is a program under Children’s Miracle Network.
